WEBVTT

00:05.714 --> 00:09.718
[lighter clinking]

00:12.429 --> 00:14.097
- Tyler, can you hear me?

00:16.725 --> 00:18.101
Look, I know you're mad.

00:21.646 --> 00:23.398
Come on, Tyler.

00:23.481 --> 00:26.192
[suspenseful music]

00:26.276 --> 00:30.196
♪ ♪

00:30.280 --> 00:33.116
Clark and I are worried.

00:33.199 --> 00:37.120
Whatever you think happened,
it's just...

00:37.203 --> 00:39.706
it's just grown-up stuff.

00:39.789 --> 00:43.084
♪ ♪

00:44.627 --> 00:45.879
[tone sounds]
- Ladies and gentlemen...

00:45.962 --> 00:49.716
- Weird time to fly.
[chuckles]

00:49.799 --> 00:50.425
- Yeah.

00:50.508 --> 00:54.345
[indistinct chatter]

00:57.766 --> 00:59.142
- She's from Alpha/Beta.

01:01.519 --> 01:04.439
- Elizabeth!

01:04.522 --> 01:06.649
Elizabeth!

01:06.733 --> 01:10.403
[indistinct chatter continues]

01:10.487 --> 01:12.864
Oh, she--she's a friend.

01:14.574 --> 01:17.577
Elizabeth!

01:17.660 --> 01:19.037
- Once you're seated,
fasten your seat belt

01:19.120 --> 01:20.330
and also make sure
your seat back

01:20.413 --> 01:24.125
and serving trays are at
their full upright position.

01:24.209 --> 01:25.877
- She mustn't have heard me.

01:27.587 --> 01:31.007
[quirky music]

01:31.090 --> 01:34.052
[indistinct chatter]

01:34.135 --> 01:36.721
♪ ♪

01:36.805 --> 01:39.098
- Sorry.
Little help.

01:39.182 --> 01:40.767
- I'll get it!

01:40.850 --> 01:47.899
♪ ♪

01:52.612 --> 01:54.823
Hi.

01:54.906 --> 01:57.408
- Clark.

01:57.492 --> 02:00.411
I saw you in LaGuardia
eating a pretzel.

02:02.372 --> 02:05.583
- So shocking, Elizabeth,
so shocking.

02:05.667 --> 02:07.502
- My lawyer called
during the layover.

02:07.585 --> 02:10.547
Tyler doesn't know.

02:10.630 --> 02:12.423
And now...
[chuckles]

02:12.507 --> 02:15.802
Oh, look,
we're in a shit indie movie.

02:17.804 --> 02:20.431
- C-can he not hear us?
- No.

02:23.143 --> 02:25.353
Why are you going to Chicago?

02:25.436 --> 02:28.898
- Well, I was still listed as
an executor of Arthur's estate.

02:32.443 --> 02:33.403
I'm...

02:33.486 --> 02:37.907
I'm responsible for getting
the body back to Mexico.

02:37.991 --> 02:40.368
I mean, I-I'm just so sorry
for Tyler.

02:40.451 --> 02:43.496
- Mm.

02:43.580 --> 02:46.416
Was it hard to remember
our names?

02:46.499 --> 02:47.917
- Whose?

02:48.001 --> 02:50.253
- All the women
that Arthur fucked.

02:50.336 --> 02:54.215
♪ ♪

02:54.299 --> 02:57.093
- I usually wasn't aware--
- You never made a mistake.

02:57.176 --> 02:59.137
- I...

02:59.220 --> 03:00.263
Elizabeth...

03:02.891 --> 03:05.393
How's Tyler doing?

03:05.476 --> 03:08.104
- Not great, but...

03:08.187 --> 03:10.064
he won't admit it.

03:10.148 --> 03:14.402
- Excuse me, sir.
You're standing in my way.

03:14.485 --> 03:16.946
- Sorry.
- Sei pazzo.

03:17.030 --> 03:19.741
Is he bothering you?
- Oh, no, she's, um...

03:19.824 --> 03:21.117
[tone sounds]
- Ladies and gentlemen,

03:21.200 --> 03:24.203
we've got a bit
of a hiccup in Chicago,

03:24.287 --> 03:25.788
and we're being diverted
to Severn City, Michigan.

03:25.872 --> 03:28.374
- You're kidding me.
- Oh.

03:28.458 --> 03:30.335
- Shouldn't be too long.

03:30.418 --> 03:31.336
- Please leave first class.

03:31.419 --> 03:36.257
- It's okay, Brian.
He's, uh--he's just a fan.

03:36.341 --> 03:39.177
- Please return to your seats
and fasten your seat belts.

03:39.260 --> 03:45.308
♪ ♪

03:59.948 --> 04:03.034
[indistinct chatter]

04:14.796 --> 04:17.507
- Ladies and gentlemen, we are
getting more information

04:17.590 --> 04:20.134
on the larger global situation
as it comes in,

04:20.218 --> 04:22.553
and we will continue
to update you.

04:22.637 --> 04:24.555
Thank you
for your understanding.

04:24.639 --> 04:27.517
[indistinct chatter continues]

04:31.396 --> 04:33.731
- We don't seem to be hearing
each other.

04:33.815 --> 04:36.025
Do you even know what
a United Nations Ambassador is?

04:36.109 --> 04:37.652
- She has been to Nepal.

04:37.735 --> 04:40.363
She has done humanitarian work
in Belize.

04:40.446 --> 04:43.491
- Hey, I'm getting a car
from the rental desk--

04:43.574 --> 04:45.368
- Brian!

04:45.451 --> 04:47.328
- Just--if you and Tyler
wanted to, um--

04:47.412 --> 04:50.540
- My assistant just got us
a jet--it's en route.

04:50.623 --> 04:51.833
- Oh, fantastic.

04:51.916 --> 04:54.377
T-to Chicago?
- Mm.

04:56.796 --> 05:00.008
- He's the agent.
I'm the nanny.

05:00.842 --> 05:02.552
- There's
the first-class lounge.

05:02.635 --> 05:03.886
Brian, let's take that.

05:03.970 --> 05:05.263
Tyler?

05:05.346 --> 05:07.598
Shay, can you get him?
Tyler!

05:10.601 --> 05:12.353
- Why?

05:12.437 --> 05:16.065
- It is your job
to get me out of here!

05:16.149 --> 05:17.692
Michi-what?

05:17.775 --> 05:20.611
- Jesus.
- I'm sorry.

05:20.695 --> 05:23.031
- [scoffs]
Don't worry about it.

05:23.114 --> 05:25.074
- Um, could you tell me where
the, uh, car rental desk is?

05:25.158 --> 05:26.743
- No cars.
Everything's rented.

05:26.826 --> 05:28.536
- I need to get to Chicago.

05:28.619 --> 05:31.581
- Well, okay, Steve Martin.
Let me call John Candy.

05:31.664 --> 05:33.374
We'll get you both back home
for Thanksgiving.

05:33.458 --> 05:36.002
- I need you to get me
on a flight, now!

05:36.085 --> 05:38.087
That is not an option.
Do you hear me?

05:38.171 --> 05:39.672
That is not an option!

05:39.756 --> 05:40.923
- Sir!

05:41.007 --> 05:44.010
I need you to take a breath.

05:44.093 --> 05:45.344
- Fuck you.

05:45.428 --> 05:47.764
- Down you get.
Down you get.

05:47.847 --> 05:49.265
- Ah!

05:49.348 --> 05:52.226
[indistinct chatter]

05:52.310 --> 05:55.313
[dramatic orchestral music]

05:55.396 --> 06:01.444
♪ ♪

06:16.542 --> 06:19.087
- Your attention,
ladies and gentlemen.

06:19.170 --> 06:21.339
all flights have been canceled
at this time.

06:21.422 --> 06:23.216
- Come on!

06:23.299 --> 06:26.803
- Deaths inside critical
international logistics firms

06:26.886 --> 06:28.429
could cause a catastrophe
in the coming days,

06:28.513 --> 06:32.934
regardless of case numbers
dramatically dropping.

06:36.062 --> 06:39.315
Cain, if you're watching this,
you need to listen to me.

06:39.398 --> 06:42.068
This is real. Take the kids
to your parents' place, now.

06:42.151 --> 06:45.655
Back roads only,
no motorways.

06:45.738 --> 06:47.323
- Excuse me.

06:49.700 --> 06:51.327
- Holy shit.

06:51.410 --> 06:53.496
[indistinct chatter]

06:56.165 --> 06:57.583
- God has a plan.

06:57.667 --> 06:59.001
- Uh-huh.

06:59.085 --> 07:01.963
Let's fucking hope so.

07:04.757 --> 07:05.925
- Hey, it's Tim.

07:06.008 --> 07:07.802
Try leaving a message.

07:07.885 --> 07:09.929
I hate phones.
Bye!

07:10.012 --> 07:12.932
- Hiya.
Um, I forgot my charger.

07:13.015 --> 07:14.976
So I'm gonna have
to borrow one.

07:16.269 --> 07:19.522
This flu seems substantial.

07:19.605 --> 07:23.526
But don't worry.
N-no one has it here, so...

07:23.609 --> 07:27.613
[indistinct chatter continues]

07:27.697 --> 07:28.447
[sighs]

07:34.954 --> 07:37.874
[dark music]

07:37.957 --> 07:44.547
♪ ♪

07:44.630 --> 07:47.800
[indistinct chatter continues]

07:50.136 --> 07:52.388
- I just heard them say

07:52.471 --> 07:55.349
they're not letting people
get off that one.

07:57.143 --> 07:59.437
The people on
that plane are sick.

07:59.520 --> 08:01.856
♪ ♪

08:01.939 --> 08:03.608
- Holy shit.

08:03.691 --> 08:07.570
I mean, they--they still
have rights as citizens.

08:07.653 --> 08:09.739
And if they need
medical attention...

08:09.822 --> 08:11.782
[indistinct conversation]

08:11.866 --> 08:13.826
- I guess it doesn't matter.

08:13.910 --> 08:15.369
This flu kills everyone.

08:15.453 --> 08:18.539
We're all dead
if they come inside here.

08:20.750 --> 08:27.840
♪ ♪

08:27.924 --> 08:29.592
Would you die for a stranger?

08:35.014 --> 08:36.807
- Probably not.

08:39.560 --> 08:41.062
Excuse me.

08:43.940 --> 08:50.988
♪ ♪

09:06.796 --> 09:09.090
- They're bringing the luggage.

09:10.883 --> 09:12.510
- Thank you.

09:15.346 --> 09:16.305
- All remaining baggage

09:16.389 --> 09:19.642
will be available
in the atrium only

09:19.725 --> 09:21.727
beneath
the "Edmund Fitzgerald."

09:21.811 --> 09:23.521
Good luck.

09:23.604 --> 09:29.652
♪ ♪

09:33.948 --> 09:35.616
- Excuse me.

09:35.700 --> 09:39.954
[chuckles] I'm such a fan.
You just have no idea.

09:40.037 --> 09:42.248
- Thank you.
- Would you mind?

09:42.331 --> 09:43.499
- Um...

09:43.582 --> 09:44.667
yeah, sure.
- [squeals]

09:49.630 --> 09:53.009
- I mean, you'd think
at a time like this...

09:53.092 --> 09:54.677
[chuckles]

09:54.760 --> 09:57.346
I mean, she's famous.
Big deal.

09:57.430 --> 09:59.056
I'll tell you what--
she won't be very famous

09:59.140 --> 10:01.642
if everyone
on the fucking planet dies.

10:03.936 --> 10:06.772
[indistinct chatter]

10:16.782 --> 10:17.366
Wow.

10:17.450 --> 10:20.036
Serious business.
[chuckles]

10:20.119 --> 10:21.579
Do you remember me?

10:21.662 --> 10:24.165
I'm a friend of your father's.

10:25.708 --> 10:27.918
Uncle Clark.

10:38.304 --> 10:41.807
I think you're very smart.

10:41.891 --> 10:45.019
[chuckles]

10:45.102 --> 10:47.688
And I think you know
exactly what call

10:47.772 --> 10:51.859
your mother got
back in New York...

10:51.942 --> 10:52.735
last night.

10:56.155 --> 10:58.199
Your father...

11:00.159 --> 11:02.078
- [sighs]

11:02.161 --> 11:04.205
- Hmm.

11:08.417 --> 11:10.878
[sighs]

11:10.961 --> 11:15.132
You know, I don't know what's
gonna happen with this flu.

11:15.216 --> 11:18.636
Civilization is a complex,
self-correcting mechanism,

11:18.719 --> 11:22.014
as complex as a person, ah...

11:22.098 --> 11:23.808
only self-aware
to a degree.

11:23.891 --> 11:26.310
[chuckles]
Eh...

11:26.394 --> 11:28.437
you understand.

11:28.521 --> 11:32.483
But whatever happens...

11:34.151 --> 11:35.986
I'm your uncle Clark.

11:47.289 --> 11:50.835
"The worst I may be yet.

11:50.918 --> 11:52.294
"The worst is not

11:52.378 --> 11:55.673
"as long as we can say...

11:55.756 --> 11:58.759
'this is the worst.'"

12:05.933 --> 12:09.145
[woman screams]

12:09.228 --> 12:12.273
M-Mom! Mom!

12:12.356 --> 12:15.609
- Does, um, she need help?

12:15.693 --> 12:18.779
- I don't know.

12:18.863 --> 12:22.700
I quit my job
a couple of hours ago.

12:22.783 --> 12:25.786
Had my gear in my truck,
thank God.

12:27.121 --> 12:28.747
- Oh.

12:33.794 --> 12:37.465
- [sighs]

12:37.548 --> 12:40.050
I think this thing
is really happening, man.

12:42.470 --> 12:45.556
You can see it out there...

12:47.391 --> 12:50.352
Kind of this...

12:50.436 --> 12:54.315
glaze in people's eyes.

12:54.398 --> 12:56.859
It's like the whole world
is just this now.

13:00.029 --> 13:04.283
- They're all heroes
on board that plane...

13:04.366 --> 13:06.202
every single one of them.

13:06.285 --> 13:10.206
[inhales deeply]

13:10.289 --> 13:12.708
We'll get through this.

13:12.791 --> 13:16.337
My optimism's intact.

13:18.631 --> 13:22.384
- You sure that's not
the liquid courage?

13:22.468 --> 13:24.470
- Probably.
- Probably.

13:24.553 --> 13:27.473
[quirky music]

13:27.556 --> 13:34.438
♪ ♪

13:34.522 --> 13:37.608
[indistinct chatter]

13:42.905 --> 13:45.241
- Can you put on
something else?

13:45.324 --> 13:50.287
♪ ♪

13:50.371 --> 13:51.747
God!
Change the fucking channel!

13:51.830 --> 13:55.417
- No!
It's my TV, bitch.

13:55.501 --> 14:02.550
♪ ♪

14:12.851 --> 14:14.520
- Clark Thompson.

14:14.603 --> 14:17.106
No smoking.

14:17.189 --> 14:18.274
I see from my files here
you've been doing some business

14:18.357 --> 14:20.484
with Goldman Sachs.

14:20.568 --> 14:24.154
- Is that my LinkedIn page?

14:24.238 --> 14:26.615
- I obviously can't let this
go wide,

14:26.699 --> 14:28.701
but I'm looking
for useful people,

14:28.784 --> 14:32.830
thoughtful people,
skilled people...

14:32.913 --> 14:33.998
like you.

14:34.081 --> 14:35.958
- Ah, I'm not sure

14:36.041 --> 14:39.378
I know
what you're talking about.

14:41.797 --> 14:44.174
- I'm talking
about zombies, man.

14:47.720 --> 14:49.179
- Good.

14:50.889 --> 14:52.308
- Stay out
of my beach community.

14:52.391 --> 14:56.103
[soft music]

14:56.186 --> 15:02.818
♪ ♪

15:11.368 --> 15:11.869
- Who's that guy?

15:14.121 --> 15:15.998
- Ladies and gentlemen,
this is Agent Nick Roker,

15:16.081 --> 15:19.460
Homeland Security,
with a little announcement.

15:19.543 --> 15:21.378
I know these are trying times,
but we need you

15:21.462 --> 15:23.505
to be a little more respectful
of the facilities here,

15:23.589 --> 15:26.467
restrooms especially.

15:26.550 --> 15:28.844
We have no further updates
for you at this time.

15:28.927 --> 15:32.348
We'll all get through
this together.

15:32.431 --> 15:33.098
Roker out.

15:33.182 --> 15:37.519
♪ ♪

15:37.603 --> 15:41.357
[lock clicks, device beeps]

15:41.440 --> 15:47.488
♪ ♪

16:16.475 --> 16:18.769
- You're grounded, fuckers.

16:21.689 --> 16:26.151
[cell phone chiming]

16:26.235 --> 16:28.028
No way.

16:28.112 --> 16:30.531
Finally, a fucking signal.

16:34.493 --> 16:37.955
- Hey, where are you?

16:38.038 --> 16:40.582
Call me.

16:40.666 --> 16:43.544
[coughs]
I wish you were here.

16:43.627 --> 16:47.506
I've been thinking about
the "I accept this" thing,

16:47.589 --> 16:50.926
Dr. Norman, and I-I do not.

16:51.009 --> 16:53.887
I-I do not accept this.

16:53.971 --> 16:56.265
[coughs]

16:56.348 --> 17:00.436
[hacking]

17:00.519 --> 17:02.688
I'm really sick.

17:02.771 --> 17:05.441
I have it.

17:05.524 --> 17:06.608
- I'm sorry.

17:06.692 --> 17:09.611
- It wasn't true, what I said.

17:09.695 --> 17:13.198
I just can't take
two weeks off.

17:13.282 --> 17:15.659
Remember that time at Jonny's?

17:15.743 --> 17:18.454
[chuckles, coughs]

17:18.537 --> 17:20.664
I love you.

17:20.748 --> 17:24.960
Why didn't you call?

17:25.043 --> 17:26.462
[coughs]
- [sobs softly]

17:26.545 --> 17:30.257
[dramatic music]

17:30.340 --> 17:37.347
♪ ♪

17:58.076 --> 17:59.828
Can I talk to you?

17:59.912 --> 18:02.331
Your assistant
never got you a jet.

18:02.414 --> 18:04.500
She's probably dead.

18:04.583 --> 18:06.168
- Oh, Uncle Clark.

18:06.251 --> 18:08.212
- Your plane's not coming.
- It will!

18:08.295 --> 18:09.838
I just have to find
my passport.

18:09.922 --> 18:12.591
- This isn't healthy
for anyone,

18:12.674 --> 18:15.010
and it sends the message
to everyone inside

18:15.093 --> 18:16.678
that you'd rather freeze
to death

18:16.762 --> 18:18.472
than be a part
of their community.

18:18.555 --> 18:20.390
- I would.

18:20.474 --> 18:22.935
- Elizabeth, powerful people
tend to crash hard

18:23.018 --> 18:26.396
when huge pockets
of false reality come down.

18:26.480 --> 18:29.066
I see it in my work
all the time.

18:29.149 --> 18:31.443
I'm a corporate consultant.

18:31.527 --> 18:33.445
- Here I thought you were
a lounge singer.

18:33.529 --> 18:35.697
- No, I'm a CEO whisperer.
- [laughs]

18:35.781 --> 18:38.033
And you get paid for that--

18:38.116 --> 18:41.203
stroking the egos
of powerful men?

18:41.286 --> 18:43.705
- I can use what I know
to protect you,

18:43.789 --> 18:44.706
all three of us,

18:44.790 --> 18:47.042
if you'll accept my help.

18:47.125 --> 18:48.961
- You sound
like a movie villain.

18:49.044 --> 18:51.755
- Tyler needs attention.
- Tyler's fine. He's with Shay.

18:51.839 --> 18:55.759
- He's sitting in front
of a plane of corpses!

18:55.843 --> 19:00.222
[quirky music]

19:00.305 --> 19:02.391
- We got to get out of here, T.

19:02.474 --> 19:04.101
- Look...

19:06.854 --> 19:08.480
[indistinct chatter]

19:08.564 --> 19:11.400
- Ladies, Agent Nick Roker,
Homeland Security.

19:11.483 --> 19:12.943
I'm putting a team together.
Maybe you can help.

19:13.026 --> 19:15.779
You ever been
to the Florida Keys?

19:15.863 --> 19:17.948
There's a little island
there called Anastasia Island.

19:18.031 --> 19:21.159
Any experience piloting a boat?

19:21.243 --> 19:23.871
I'm looking for people
with specific skill sets.

19:23.954 --> 19:25.664
Ladies and gentlemen,

19:25.747 --> 19:27.958
this is Agent Nick Roker,
Homeland Security,

19:28.041 --> 19:30.168
with a quick reminder
that all restricted areas

19:30.252 --> 19:31.837
are still off-limits

19:31.920 --> 19:35.173
to anyone other
than authorized personnel.

19:35.257 --> 19:41.305
♪ ♪

19:46.018 --> 19:48.478
Uh, I've said this
a couple of times now,

19:48.562 --> 19:51.106
but, please,
anyone with extra trash,

19:51.189 --> 19:53.567
especially things that
can rot, put it out front.

19:53.650 --> 19:56.486
Roker out.

19:58.530 --> 20:01.325
- Jerry.

20:01.408 --> 20:03.285
Jerry, Jerry, Jerry.

20:05.120 --> 20:08.373
What a wicked web
we fucking weave.

20:08.457 --> 20:16.256
♪ ♪

20:22.179 --> 20:25.390
Agent Roker, you naughty boy.

20:25.474 --> 20:32.522
♪ ♪

20:45.452 --> 20:47.412
[indistinct chatter]

20:47.496 --> 20:55.295
♪ ♪

21:06.306 --> 21:09.226
[indistinct chatter
grows louder]

21:13.105 --> 21:14.439
- What's happened?

21:15.524 --> 21:18.110
- Mr. Homeland Security
apparently went around

21:18.193 --> 21:20.696
and told
all the people he liked

21:20.779 --> 21:25.117
that he's leaving for
a better world--Miami Beach.

21:25.200 --> 21:28.036
- Movie star's nanny left.

21:28.120 --> 21:30.455
- And the Italian boyfriend.

21:30.539 --> 21:33.291
- I'm surprised
she didn't go with.

21:33.375 --> 21:35.877
- Do we know how many he took?

21:35.961 --> 21:39.089
- He took mostly women.

21:39.172 --> 21:40.716
- The whole soccer team...

21:40.799 --> 21:43.385
except the goalie.

21:43.468 --> 21:46.179
[indistinct chatter continues]

21:57.566 --> 21:59.151
- Um...

21:59.234 --> 22:01.903
uh, could I have
your attention, please?

22:01.987 --> 22:04.239
Could you turn around?
This is important.

22:04.322 --> 22:05.949
Sorry, this is important!

22:06.033 --> 22:08.410
Could you turn around?

22:12.664 --> 22:14.499
Um...

22:14.583 --> 22:17.753
this is the best thing that
could have possibly happened.

22:17.836 --> 22:20.422
Okay, they left.

22:20.505 --> 22:22.257
They didn't invite you, or me,

22:22.340 --> 22:26.011
because they thought
they were better than you.

22:26.094 --> 22:30.057
They thought they deserved
to live and you didn't.

22:30.140 --> 22:33.894
They were in it for themselves.

22:33.977 --> 22:37.230
And the only problem
with their plan is...

22:37.314 --> 22:38.815
they were taken in
by a janitorial con man.

22:38.899 --> 22:40.317
- What?
- What?

22:40.400 --> 22:44.571
- Late last night,
after some investigation,

22:44.654 --> 22:48.366
it came to my attention
that, uh, our Agent Roker,

22:48.450 --> 22:53.747
who's been in charge since
the early days, was a fraud.

22:53.830 --> 22:56.458
- Whoa. What?
- Yeah.

22:56.541 --> 22:58.293
His real name is Jerry Mercer,

22:58.376 --> 23:00.295
and up until a week
and a half ago,

23:00.378 --> 23:03.757
he was the night custodian
of this airport.

23:03.840 --> 23:07.219
- What?
- No way.

23:07.302 --> 23:09.846
- Did any of you ever stop
to wonder why there was

23:09.930 --> 23:13.892
a Homeland Security team
at Severn City, Michigan?

23:13.975 --> 23:15.310
No?

23:15.394 --> 23:16.311
He was an opportunist,

23:16.394 --> 23:18.980
and he took advantage
of your fear

23:19.064 --> 23:21.733
and the illusion of his power,

23:21.817 --> 23:24.820
and he has likely just led
all those people

23:24.903 --> 23:27.114
to their death.

23:27.197 --> 23:29.157
I mean, w-who was even flying?
Who was--

23:29.241 --> 23:31.827
- Our captain.
[indistinct chatter]

23:31.910 --> 23:32.994
- Huh. Irrelevant.

23:33.078 --> 23:35.872
In fact, good. Good.

23:35.956 --> 23:37.249
- But we had a pilot.
Now we don't.

23:37.332 --> 23:39.292
H-how is that good?

23:39.376 --> 23:41.002
- Because you need a pilot when
there's somewhere to go, yeah?

23:41.086 --> 23:43.046
And where do we have to go?

23:43.130 --> 23:46.341
What appointments matter now?

23:46.424 --> 23:50.637
We have to abandon
the future, okay?

23:50.720 --> 23:55.433
All that matters is the now
and what got us to this point,

23:55.517 --> 23:58.645
because the past is a map,
and it got us here,

23:58.728 --> 24:00.564
and here, at this airport,

24:00.647 --> 24:04.526
we have won
the post-apocalyptic lottery!

24:04.609 --> 24:09.281
And that plane leaving
just made all our shares go up!

24:09.364 --> 24:10.824
Okay?

24:10.907 --> 24:13.285
The drawbridge is closed,

24:13.368 --> 24:15.036
because Jerry Mercer,

24:15.120 --> 24:17.414
the fucking coward
Jerry Mercer,

24:17.497 --> 24:20.542
has effectively tripled
our food supply.

24:20.625 --> 24:22.210
Here we are...

24:22.294 --> 24:24.087
with much of our hierarchy
of needs already met.

24:24.171 --> 24:27.382
We have shelter.
We have food.

24:27.465 --> 24:29.301
- That's right.
- Yeah.

24:29.384 --> 24:33.555
- We're a community.
[indistinct chatter]

24:33.638 --> 24:35.056
And we're tucked away
in a place

24:35.140 --> 24:38.935
no one is ever gonna find us.

24:39.019 --> 24:40.061
- How do you know
he was faking, though?

24:40.145 --> 24:43.064
Maybe you made this up.

24:43.148 --> 24:44.941
- You think I made this up?

24:45.025 --> 24:46.067
For fuck's sake, Constance,
look at it.

24:46.151 --> 24:49.654
Look at it.
- It's true.

24:51.990 --> 24:55.285
I knew Mercer.

24:57.037 --> 24:59.414
Thought he was harmless...

24:59.497 --> 25:01.625
just doing his thing.

25:04.502 --> 25:07.505
But when I said something,
he threatened to kill me.

25:10.842 --> 25:13.929
- He told me
he would take me...

25:14.012 --> 25:17.474
but I'd have to leave my child.

25:17.557 --> 25:19.517
- [scoffs]

25:19.601 --> 25:23.271
I confronted him last night
with Miles and Elizabeth...

25:23.355 --> 25:25.774
and instead
of facing you today,

25:25.857 --> 25:29.611
he snuck away in the night
with the female soccer team...

25:32.155 --> 25:33.782
Except for the goalie.

25:33.865 --> 25:35.408
- I never trusted that guy.
- Yeah, me neither!

25:35.492 --> 25:40.455
- See, everybody shits
on the goalie, you know?

25:40.538 --> 25:43.124
They like the strikers,
the flash.

25:43.208 --> 25:46.753
But the goalie--
that's how you win things.

25:46.836 --> 25:47.879
- He's right.

25:47.963 --> 25:51.841
- And we're in this together,
and we're a family now.

25:53.927 --> 25:56.012
And I say fuck Jerry Mercer.
Fuck him.

25:56.096 --> 25:57.180
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

25:57.264 --> 26:00.141
- That's right.
- Yeah.

26:00.225 --> 26:01.226
Fuck him.

26:01.309 --> 26:02.394
- Fuck him!

26:02.477 --> 26:02.936
- Fuck Jerry Mercer!

26:03.019 --> 26:06.314
[all shouting]

26:06.398 --> 26:09.150
- Fuck him.
- Fuck that guy.

26:09.234 --> 26:09.985
- Fuck Jerry Mercer.
- Fuck him.

26:10.068 --> 26:11.987
- Fuck Jerry Mercer!

26:12.070 --> 26:17.867
[shouting continues]

26:17.951 --> 26:21.997
- Well played, Marc Antony.

26:22.080 --> 26:23.999
You're a star.

26:24.082 --> 26:26.793
[soft music]

26:26.876 --> 26:29.170
[laughs]

26:29.254 --> 26:32.007
- We've really got
something here.

26:32.090 --> 26:33.883
You know?

26:33.967 --> 26:36.344
The--the four of us,
including Tyler,

26:36.428 --> 26:38.638
'cause I-I don't discount him.

26:38.722 --> 26:41.099
You know, the sympathy
for the children, the child.

26:41.182 --> 26:44.477
Some connotation of Arthur.

26:46.104 --> 26:47.939
Mm.

26:48.023 --> 26:50.191
Your celebrity
is a little less relevant

26:50.275 --> 26:52.777
in a post-apocalyptic context.

26:52.861 --> 26:54.362
- [laughs]
- I know.

26:54.446 --> 26:56.531
No, but it still has
a sparkle to it.

26:56.614 --> 26:58.366
They remember your fame.
- Oh, that's true.

26:58.450 --> 27:01.536
- And, Miles, your connection
to a federal institution

27:01.619 --> 27:03.830
gives you
the natural leader profile.

27:03.913 --> 27:05.957
- Why do we need a leader
at all?

27:06.041 --> 27:09.461
- Because, Tyler,
leaders give us hope.

27:09.544 --> 27:11.546
And we won't survive here
long enough

27:11.629 --> 27:13.006
to repopulate the Earth

27:13.089 --> 27:15.717
if the people here
don't feel hopeful.

27:15.800 --> 27:17.177
- Maybe we shouldn't, though.

27:17.260 --> 27:21.014
- Shouldn't what, Tyler?

27:21.097 --> 27:22.932
- Repopulate.

27:24.642 --> 27:26.978
- That's a little bleak,
isn't it?

27:27.062 --> 27:29.689
- [chuckles]
No, it's cute.

27:34.778 --> 27:37.072
- My hot spot
still works at night--

27:37.155 --> 27:39.407
German satellite.

27:39.491 --> 27:42.619
We could download Wikipedia,
whatever else we can find.

27:42.702 --> 27:44.537
- Good idea.

27:44.621 --> 27:46.831
Yeah, get whatever you can
about, uh, electricity,

27:46.915 --> 27:48.083
engineering.

27:48.166 --> 27:51.002
- Shakespeare.

27:51.086 --> 27:54.005
- So what, it'll be a...

27:54.089 --> 27:55.090
a triumvirate?

27:55.173 --> 27:59.052
- Mm.
- Yeah.

27:59.135 --> 28:01.096
But with four.

28:01.179 --> 28:04.099
[dramatic music]

28:04.182 --> 28:08.353
♪ ♪

28:08.436 --> 28:11.189
- Go ahead. Try it.
Santa can hear.

28:11.272 --> 28:13.775
- I just--
I just want my brother.

28:15.944 --> 28:19.322
- Santa's elves can make
your brother.

28:19.406 --> 28:21.199
It's like AI.

28:21.282 --> 28:24.828
- Where are the children?
- In the tower.

28:24.911 --> 28:27.414
Tyler had an idea.

28:27.497 --> 28:29.791
- Seriously, try it.
Santa talks to dead people.

28:32.877 --> 28:35.255
You'll feel better
if you say something.

28:35.338 --> 28:37.382
Doesn't matter
if he can hear you.

28:37.465 --> 28:40.051
♪ ♪

28:40.135 --> 28:42.637
- Hey, Ryan,
I hope you're good...

28:44.681 --> 28:46.933
And you get good things
for Christmas like "Fortnite."

28:47.016 --> 28:49.519
Right?

28:49.602 --> 28:55.066
♪ ♪

28:55.150 --> 28:57.235
We play in my head.

28:57.318 --> 28:59.904
- Okay, kids, downstairs.

28:59.988 --> 29:02.532
You're not supposed
to be up here.

29:04.534 --> 29:06.202
Come on.

29:06.286 --> 29:08.663
[door opens]

29:08.746 --> 29:10.832
How did you get up here?

29:10.915 --> 29:12.750
- It was working.

29:12.834 --> 29:13.877
[door closes]

29:40.278 --> 29:43.948
- Hi, Arthur.

29:44.032 --> 29:45.200
Are you there?

29:45.283 --> 29:48.119
Hi, it's Clark.

29:48.203 --> 29:51.122
Yeah. Yeah, no,
good to hear from you, too.

29:51.206 --> 29:55.210
Listen, I'm sitting here
with your son,

29:55.293 --> 29:58.796
and I'm sorry to say it,
but he's being a real knob.

29:58.880 --> 30:01.716
Yeah, asking all the other kids
to pretend,

30:01.799 --> 30:03.384
but he won't play the game.

30:03.468 --> 30:07.555
Was he always like this?

30:07.639 --> 30:08.806
Yes, he's here.

30:08.890 --> 30:11.518
Yes, right here. Okay.

30:11.601 --> 30:13.353
Okay.

30:36.876 --> 30:38.127
- Hey, Dad.

30:39.504 --> 30:40.922
Sorry I didn't get a chance

30:41.005 --> 30:43.591
to come see your play
in Chicago.

30:43.675 --> 30:45.468
I really wanted to.

30:45.552 --> 30:47.512
I was really excited.

30:47.595 --> 30:50.223
Mom had a night shoot.

30:50.306 --> 30:53.059
She really tried.

30:53.142 --> 30:56.646
Anyway, it's cool
that you did "King Lear."

30:56.729 --> 30:58.898
I don't know what else to say.

31:01.818 --> 31:04.445
I'm glad I saw you last month,

31:04.529 --> 31:06.948
but...

31:07.031 --> 31:09.284
I wish I could see you again.

31:09.367 --> 31:16.416
♪ ♪

31:18.876 --> 31:20.878
- Now, how'd that feel?

31:23.506 --> 31:26.884
- Okay, so no one panic,

31:26.968 --> 31:28.803
but the electrical grid
must have gone down,

31:28.886 --> 31:31.180
because we switched
to generator overnight.

31:31.264 --> 31:34.267
That means, though,
we'll be using power sparingly.

31:34.350 --> 31:36.477
- How sparingly?
- Yeah, exactly.

31:36.561 --> 31:38.396
- No lights during the day.

31:38.479 --> 31:40.732
We'll keep one TV on
for news updates.

31:40.815 --> 31:44.485
And please don't prioritize
charging your personal devices.

31:44.569 --> 31:46.779
- We need the Internet, though.
- Yeah.

31:46.863 --> 31:50.658
- As far as we know,
the Internet is gone.

31:50.742 --> 31:52.368
Right, Tyler?

31:54.203 --> 31:55.496
- No more Internet.

31:55.580 --> 31:57.332
- Oh.
- Oh.

31:57.415 --> 31:58.958
- The people who ran
the airport were planning

31:59.042 --> 32:00.877
to install solar panels
on all the hangar roofs.

32:00.960 --> 32:03.671
Now, I'm thinking,
between these

32:03.755 --> 32:07.842
and all the old airplane
batteries we got in storage...

32:07.925 --> 32:09.969
we could really rig something.

32:12.430 --> 32:15.516
- Really?
A-and you know how to?

32:15.600 --> 32:18.186
- Yeah.
- I'm impressed.

32:19.479 --> 32:23.232
- And, technically...

32:25.443 --> 32:28.071
We could...

32:28.154 --> 32:30.490
we could last forever.

32:32.408 --> 32:35.495
- Mile--Miles, I...

32:35.578 --> 32:38.498
I'm sorry, I can't.

32:40.416 --> 32:42.043
- Well, why not?

32:43.419 --> 32:45.838
- I'm in mourning.

32:45.922 --> 32:48.007
I had someone.

32:51.469 --> 32:53.638
But this is all brilliant.

32:53.721 --> 32:56.557
[The Impressions' (Man,
Oh Man) I Want to Go Back]

32:56.641 --> 33:01.312
♪ ♪

33:01.396 --> 33:04.315
♪ Man, oh, man ♪

33:04.399 --> 33:06.609
♪ Have you been to Spain ♪

33:06.693 --> 33:08.528
[indistinct chatter]

33:08.611 --> 33:10.863
♪ Where the joy
of laughing people ♪

33:10.947 --> 33:13.157
♪ Make you happy again? ♪

33:13.241 --> 33:15.076
♪ ♪

33:15.159 --> 33:17.870
♪ Women so pretty ♪

33:17.954 --> 33:20.790
♪ Even more so at night ♪

33:20.873 --> 33:23.543
♪ While in the streets
their dance ♪

33:23.626 --> 33:26.587
♪ Brings onto you
such delight ♪

33:26.671 --> 33:29.590
♪ And, man, oh, man ♪

33:29.674 --> 33:33.928
♪ Before you go home ♪

33:34.011 --> 33:36.097
♪ Catch a flight on ♪

33:36.180 --> 33:40.643
♪ To the wonders of Rome ♪

33:40.727 --> 33:43.104
♪ Italy's beauty ♪

33:43.187 --> 33:45.606
♪ May put on the show ♪

33:45.690 --> 33:49.360
♪ To arouse all your love ♪

33:49.444 --> 33:51.320
♪ And make your heart grow ♪

33:51.404 --> 33:54.699
- You're missing the party.

33:54.782 --> 33:56.993
- [sighs]

33:57.076 --> 33:59.620
♪ ♪

33:59.704 --> 34:03.166
My hot spot stopped working.

34:03.249 --> 34:06.127
This is the last thing
I downloaded.

34:06.210 --> 34:08.629
What if I just deleted it?

34:09.338 --> 34:11.632
- [sighs]

34:11.716 --> 34:14.469
I mean,
we'd just invent it again.

34:14.552 --> 34:17.472
♪ ♪

34:17.555 --> 34:19.265
Sorry, can you just put
that away for a second?

34:19.348 --> 34:24.145
♪ ♪

34:24.228 --> 34:25.480
Sorry.

34:25.563 --> 34:30.485
♪ ♪

34:30.568 --> 34:32.361
Look, I-I think
that we both know

34:32.445 --> 34:35.156
that these last years
in Germany, um...

34:37.366 --> 34:40.369
[grunts]

34:40.453 --> 34:43.748
What your father did
really hurt me.

34:43.831 --> 34:47.585
♪ ♪

34:47.668 --> 34:51.714
I don't know what it is
about being here, but I...

34:51.798 --> 34:54.091
I don't know, um...

34:54.175 --> 34:58.513
It seems like maybe there's
something good happening...

34:58.596 --> 35:00.264
with us.

35:00.348 --> 35:04.310
♪ ♪

35:04.393 --> 35:06.229
Am I crazy?

35:06.312 --> 35:08.523
Do you feel it, too?

35:08.606 --> 35:10.817
♪ ♪

35:10.900 --> 35:14.904
- Maybe it's just
because Dad's dead.

35:14.987 --> 35:21.035
♪ ♪

35:30.628 --> 35:33.923
- He left you something.

35:34.006 --> 35:37.677
It's, uh--it's more a symbol
than anything,

35:37.760 --> 35:40.555
but I had it in my bag, so...

35:40.638 --> 35:45.393
♪ ♪

35:45.476 --> 35:47.144
- The art's cool.

35:47.228 --> 35:50.773
- The MC on the cover
is for Miranda Carroll,

35:50.857 --> 35:53.442
who was
your father's first wife.

35:55.361 --> 35:57.196
- I remember her.

35:58.739 --> 36:03.703
- He sent it to me, um,
a couple of weeks ago.

36:03.786 --> 36:06.789
And I got it in the mail,
and I...

36:06.873 --> 36:08.249
I kept it from you.

36:11.210 --> 36:11.919
[sighs]

36:12.003 --> 36:15.965
I-I've been doing that
for years.

36:19.302 --> 36:22.263
He's been sending you letters
since the divorce,

36:22.346 --> 36:24.599
and, uh...

36:24.682 --> 36:27.977
I burn them.

36:35.318 --> 36:36.986
- Why?

36:40.907 --> 36:42.783
- Because I'm selfish.

36:42.867 --> 36:45.870
[strange dramatic music]

36:45.953 --> 36:52.460
♪ ♪

36:57.006 --> 36:59.508
[sighs]

37:02.970 --> 37:10.019
♪ ♪

37:12.271 --> 37:15.316
[indistinct chatter]

37:15.399 --> 37:22.198
♪ ♪

37:28.162 --> 37:30.039
- Everything all right?

37:32.041 --> 37:36.212
- He can tell
when people are lying.

37:36.295 --> 37:37.546
[sighs]

37:37.630 --> 37:41.676
- Well, what did you lie
to him about?

37:41.759 --> 37:43.636
- That Arthur kept trying.

37:48.516 --> 37:51.894
- Who wants some
jala-fucking-peño poppers?

37:51.978 --> 37:55.064
[excited chatter]

38:37.815 --> 38:41.777
[clattering]

38:44.321 --> 38:46.949
[person wheezes, grunts]

38:47.033 --> 38:50.745
[suspenseful music]

38:50.828 --> 38:57.877
♪ ♪

39:34.830 --> 39:38.667
[indistinct chatter]

39:50.429 --> 39:51.472
- [chuckles]

39:57.603 --> 40:01.649
Two weeks feels
like an eternity here.

40:01.732 --> 40:04.568
- How so?

40:04.652 --> 40:05.319
- Well, you know...

40:08.572 --> 40:11.158
- No. I don't know.
- [chuckles]

40:11.242 --> 40:12.493
Earlier...

40:12.576 --> 40:14.036
- Oh.

40:14.120 --> 40:16.455
Right.
- When you...

40:16.539 --> 40:18.457
- Me?
- Mm.

40:19.834 --> 40:21.919
- Zombie!

40:22.002 --> 40:25.589
[people screaming]

40:25.673 --> 40:28.217
- Tyler!
- Oh, my God!

40:28.300 --> 40:31.887
- Tyler, who's that man?

40:31.971 --> 40:33.806
- It's okay.

40:33.889 --> 40:34.515
He survived.

40:34.598 --> 40:36.183
He was
on the Gitchegumee plane.

40:36.267 --> 40:38.352
- Tyler, come here.
Come here to me!

40:38.435 --> 40:39.895
- No. No.
He's probably infected!

40:39.979 --> 40:42.731
- He's not.
He has to be immune.

40:42.815 --> 40:45.317
He didn't get it,
but they all did.

40:45.401 --> 40:47.653
This means there's
still people out there.

40:47.736 --> 40:50.781
- Tyler. Tyler, come here.
Stop touching that man! Please!

40:50.865 --> 40:52.449
- Look, please.
P-please.

40:52.533 --> 40:54.493
[concerned chatter]

40:54.577 --> 40:55.870
- Miles, Miles,
what are you doing?

40:55.953 --> 40:56.704
Put the gun down.

40:56.787 --> 40:59.748
[gunshot]

41:01.959 --> 41:06.088
[all screaming]

41:06.172 --> 41:08.382
- What the fuck, Miles?
Put the gun down! Put it down!

41:08.465 --> 41:10.843
- Jesus Christ!
They're both infected now.

41:10.926 --> 41:11.886
- Miles, put the gun down!

41:11.969 --> 41:14.555
- Elizabeth, I need you
to get outside right now.

41:14.638 --> 41:16.056
- He's wasn't sick.
He was immune.

41:16.140 --> 41:17.308
- We don't know
there is such a thing!

41:17.391 --> 41:18.726
- Oh, it just got proven,
you idiot!

41:18.809 --> 41:19.685
- What should I do?
- Take them out.

41:19.768 --> 41:23.063
- Just get them out of here.
[all shouting]

41:23.147 --> 41:25.858
- Garrett, shut the fuck up!

41:25.941 --> 41:29.069
We are not monsters!

41:29.153 --> 41:30.863
- Tell him to put the gun down.

41:30.946 --> 41:33.449
- Clark?
- Clark.

41:33.532 --> 41:34.950
- Um...

41:35.034 --> 41:37.244
we'll quarantine them.
- Fine. Quarantine.

41:37.328 --> 41:40.331
- Okay? The--the private plane
in Hangar G,

41:40.414 --> 41:43.292
the batteries work,
right, Miles?

41:43.375 --> 41:45.252
Miles?
- Yeah.

41:45.336 --> 41:47.838
- Okay, good. There'll be heat.
There'll be food.

41:47.922 --> 41:50.341
We'll keep them there
for a week, then we'll know.

41:50.424 --> 41:53.260
- That's not enough.
[all shouting]

41:53.344 --> 41:55.221
- We want our friends
back in our community.

41:55.304 --> 41:56.597
- A month, at least.

41:56.680 --> 41:58.641
- Clark...

41:58.724 --> 42:00.935
a week's not enough.

42:01.018 --> 42:01.936
A month.

42:02.019 --> 42:03.103
- A month?
- Yes.

42:03.187 --> 42:04.563
- A month?
- Okay, yes.

42:04.647 --> 42:05.898
- A month.
- Yeah.

42:05.981 --> 42:07.816
- Okay.
That's a fair compromise.

42:07.900 --> 42:09.318
- Fine, fine, a month.
We're going.

42:09.401 --> 42:11.445
We're going.
We're going.

42:11.528 --> 42:14.490
[dramatic music]

42:14.573 --> 42:18.661
♪ ♪

42:18.744 --> 42:21.580
[concerned chatter]

42:21.664 --> 42:24.583
- "When your people go out
to battle their enemy,

42:24.667 --> 42:25.793
by whatever way
you send them..."

42:25.876 --> 42:28.379
- You did the right thing.
- "And they pray to the Lord.

42:28.462 --> 42:31.757
"Then hear in heaven
their prayer

42:31.840 --> 42:34.635
and their pleading,
and maintain their cause."

42:37.221 --> 42:39.390
"When they sin against you,

42:39.473 --> 42:43.143
"for there is no person
who does not sin,

42:43.227 --> 42:44.436
"and you are angry with them

42:44.520 --> 42:48.315
"and turn them over
to the enemy,

42:48.399 --> 42:53.112
"if they repent and implore
your favor, saying,

42:53.195 --> 42:56.365
"'We have sinned
and done wrong.

42:56.448 --> 42:58.951
We have acted wickedly...'"

42:59.034 --> 43:01.745
- You haven't looked up
from that thing in three weeks.

43:01.829 --> 43:05.332
♪ ♪

43:05.416 --> 43:06.959
- There's no before.
- What are you doing?

43:07.042 --> 43:09.712
- There's no before.
There's no before.

43:09.795 --> 43:11.630
There's no before.

43:11.714 --> 43:16.760
- "If they return to you
with all their heart

43:16.844 --> 43:18.804
"and all their soul

43:18.887 --> 43:20.973
"in the land of their enemies

43:21.056 --> 43:23.392
who have taken them
captive"...

43:24.727 --> 43:29.690
"Then hear their prayer
and their pleading in heaven,

43:29.773 --> 43:31.775
your dwelling place..."

43:31.859 --> 43:38.907
♪ ♪

43:55.716 --> 43:57.384
- Everything okay?

43:57.468 --> 43:58.886
- What are you wearing?

43:58.969 --> 44:00.804
- I, uh...

44:00.888 --> 44:02.306
The folks inside

44:02.389 --> 44:03.223
said they'd feel
a little bit more comfortable

44:03.307 --> 44:05.684
if you wore these, too.

44:07.394 --> 44:09.605
It's just for a little while.

44:09.688 --> 44:09.897
That okay?

44:09.980 --> 44:14.068
♪ ♪

44:14.151 --> 44:15.861
- I told you.

44:15.944 --> 44:22.951
♪ ♪

44:28.582 --> 44:31.835
- How's that, Clark?

44:31.919 --> 44:33.796
- Perfect.

44:33.879 --> 44:37.174
- "And forgive your people
who have sinned against you

44:37.257 --> 44:40.302
"and all their wrongdoings

44:40.386 --> 44:43.931
"which they have committed
against you.

44:44.014 --> 44:46.683
"And make them objects
of compassion

44:46.767 --> 44:50.729
"before those who have
taken them captive...

44:50.813 --> 44:52.856
so that they will have
compassion on them."

44:52.940 --> 44:57.111
♪ ♪

44:57.194 --> 44:59.655
Let us pray.

44:59.738 --> 45:06.412
♪ ♪

45:08.789 --> 45:11.250
- What are you doing?
- I'm making a museum--

45:11.333 --> 45:14.002
a tribute
to the best of the old days,

45:14.086 --> 45:16.505
a reminder of how good
we used to have it...

45:16.588 --> 45:21.468
something to aim for,
to get back to.

45:21.552 --> 45:25.764
Talking to the dead through
the radio system feels macabre.

45:25.848 --> 45:28.225
This will be better.

45:28.308 --> 45:30.269
- He doesn't sleep.

45:30.352 --> 45:35.357
Since then, he was always....

45:35.441 --> 45:37.609
confused about ghosts,

45:37.693 --> 45:40.696
but this--this
has brought out something...

45:40.779 --> 45:42.531
else.

45:45.159 --> 45:46.618
There was bullying in Berlin.

45:46.702 --> 45:47.536
- Tyler processed
the quarantine

45:47.619 --> 45:52.040
as some kind
of personal humiliation.

45:52.124 --> 45:55.752
He needs to grow up
and get over it.

45:55.836 --> 45:57.504
- Do you hate Tyler
because you hated Arthur?

45:57.588 --> 46:00.466
- [scoffs]
I don't hate Tyler.

46:00.549 --> 46:01.925
- But you did hate Arthur.

46:02.009 --> 46:04.052
- Why?
You think I was jealous of him?

46:04.136 --> 46:05.762
Because that's what
he thought, too.

46:05.846 --> 46:09.183
I beat him out for Antonio
in "The Merchant of Venice."

46:09.266 --> 46:10.350
- [laughs]

46:10.434 --> 46:11.351
- And he
could never understand

46:11.435 --> 46:13.937
the fact that I wasn't jealous.

46:14.021 --> 46:14.897
Arthur was pathetic.

46:14.980 --> 46:17.900
He was a B-list loser
who surrounded himself

46:17.983 --> 46:19.943
with C-list trophy duds
like yourself.

46:20.027 --> 46:21.528
- Oh, yeah.

46:21.612 --> 46:23.197
- And he threw away
the only worthwhile wife

46:23.280 --> 46:24.865
he had in Miranda,

46:24.948 --> 46:27.034
who he never got over,
by the way.

46:27.117 --> 46:30.829
He was a shit father,
a shit husband, which you know,

46:30.913 --> 46:33.749
and he died onstage
in a puddle of his own piss,

46:33.832 --> 46:36.126
desperate to be taken
seriously,

46:36.210 --> 46:38.378
trying to do "King Lear."

46:38.462 --> 46:41.590
And still, I loved him!

46:43.258 --> 46:45.093
- Everyone loved him.

46:47.846 --> 46:50.057
I mean...

46:50.140 --> 46:52.476
it takes every ounce
of your energy every day

46:52.559 --> 46:55.896
to get people
to even like you...

46:55.979 --> 46:59.608
to actually listen
to the sentences that you say,

46:59.691 --> 47:01.443
but Art...

47:01.527 --> 47:03.737
[sighs]

47:03.820 --> 47:06.365
Art didn't have to try.

47:08.659 --> 47:10.619
That must feel awful.

47:20.587 --> 47:22.339
- [scoffs]

47:22.422 --> 47:25.259
Tyler will thrive here.

47:25.342 --> 47:28.637
I haven't betrayed him, even
if you seem to think I have.

47:28.720 --> 47:33.600
In fact, I saved his life
and yours.

47:33.684 --> 47:36.812
We all know it was Arthur
who damaged Tyler.

47:36.895 --> 47:40.983
All of us, we're all
the fucking wreckage.

47:41.066 --> 47:41.858
- Yeah, you're right.
You're right.

47:41.942 --> 47:44.278
- Elizabeth, we have
to stick together.

47:44.361 --> 47:48.282
We can't let a child play us
off against one another.

47:48.365 --> 47:51.243
- I, uh--I know.

47:51.326 --> 47:53.036
[suspenseful music]

47:53.120 --> 48:00.919
♪ ♪

48:30.407 --> 48:33.076
- Arthur?

48:33.160 --> 48:34.953
Are you there?

48:36.663 --> 48:38.457
It's Clark.

48:40.417 --> 48:45.547
I miss you, old friend...

48:45.631 --> 48:47.966
despite myself.

48:48.634 --> 48:52.846
Listen, I really regret...

48:52.929 --> 48:57.100
what I said the last time
we spoke...

48:57.184 --> 48:59.311
in Chicago.

49:01.772 --> 49:05.484
I have tried
to protect your boy.

49:08.111 --> 49:10.739
But I don't know
how to anymore.

49:12.949 --> 49:16.536
H-he's like you in his way--

49:16.620 --> 49:21.375
bold, indifferent to authority,

49:21.458 --> 49:24.753
singular...

49:24.836 --> 49:27.005
but he's a destroyer.

49:29.216 --> 49:31.927
And you were never a destroyer.

49:32.010 --> 49:38.058
♪ ♪

49:41.353 --> 49:45.148
I-I mean something here
to these people.

49:45.232 --> 49:50.237
♪ ♪

49:50.320 --> 49:53.073
I've got responsibilities
to everybody now.

49:55.951 --> 49:59.413
And I don't think
I've done anything wrong.

49:59.496 --> 50:03.750
♪ ♪

50:03.834 --> 50:07.170
But it's time for Tyler
and Elizabeth to go.

50:07.254 --> 50:12.300
♪ ♪

50:12.384 --> 50:14.594
- Uncle Clark?

50:14.678 --> 50:21.601
♪ ♪

50:21.685 --> 50:24.187
- Tyler?

50:24.271 --> 50:25.272
Where are you?

50:25.355 --> 50:27.607
Were--were you--

50:27.691 --> 50:29.735
Because I didn't mean--

50:29.818 --> 50:31.445
- I'm in the death.

50:31.528 --> 50:38.577
♪ ♪

50:44.291 --> 50:45.917
- Elizabeth.

50:46.001 --> 50:48.462
Elizabeth!
Constance! Miles!

50:48.545 --> 50:49.921
Who's down there?

50:50.005 --> 50:52.549
- I'm here. What is it?
- It's Tyler.

50:52.632 --> 50:54.301
He's on board the Gitchegumee.

50:54.384 --> 50:57.387
- Why?

50:57.471 --> 51:01.141
- Tyler, what are you
doing on board that plane?

51:02.726 --> 51:06.354
- Setting all of you free.

51:07.564 --> 51:09.483
- Gate 105!

51:09.566 --> 51:16.615
♪ ♪

51:17.783 --> 51:19.826
The jet is on fire.

51:19.910 --> 51:21.703
He set it on fire!

51:21.787 --> 51:24.498
Tyler is still on board!

51:24.581 --> 51:30.295
♪ ♪

51:30.378 --> 51:33.465
- Tyler!

51:33.548 --> 51:35.300
[shouts indistinctly]

51:35.383 --> 51:37.552
Tyler!

51:37.636 --> 51:39.304
Tyler!

51:39.387 --> 51:40.889
No!

51:40.972 --> 51:43.517
[shouts]
Tyler!

51:43.600 --> 51:46.728
[explosion]

51:46.812 --> 51:49.022
No, Tyler!
[cries]

51:49.105 --> 51:50.649
- Elizabeth--

51:50.732 --> 51:52.359
- Tyler! No!

51:52.442 --> 51:55.278
- Elizabeth--
- [shouting indistinctly]

51:55.362 --> 51:57.030
- No.

51:57.113 --> 51:58.448
Shh, shh, shh.

51:58.532 --> 52:02.118
- [sobbing]

52:02.202 --> 52:08.250
♪ ♪

52:22.848 --> 52:25.934
[continues sobbing]

52:30.355 --> 52:32.315
[dramatic music]

52:32.399 --> 52:37.779
♪ ♪

52:37.863 --> 52:40.574
- But soft, behold!

52:40.657 --> 52:42.075
Lo, where it comes again!

52:42.158 --> 52:44.703
I'll cross it though
it blast me.

52:44.786 --> 52:47.622
Stay, illusion!

52:47.706 --> 52:52.460
If thou hast any sound
or use of voice, speak to me.

52:54.421 --> 52:55.505
If there be any good thing
to be done

52:55.589 --> 53:00.468
that may to thee do ease
and grace to me, speak to me.

53:02.262 --> 53:04.180
If thou art privy
to thy country's fate,

53:04.264 --> 53:07.517
which happily foreknowing
may avoid, O, speak!

53:08.518 --> 53:11.605
Speak!

53:11.688 --> 53:12.981
Speak!
